{
  "texts": [
    "This result was supported by the teachers' complaints that most students were not able to use Vocabulary in academic wordlists.",
    "They were just familiar with words of everyday life and common topics.",
    "Teachers also added that the students were used to writing with verbs rather than nouns or noun phrases.",
    "Additionally, they explained that students might make spelling mistakes with long words, especially four-or fivesyllable ones.",
    "182 \"Students still leave some ideas incompletely addressed because they spend too much time trying to use a wide and complex range of structures."
  ]
}